<TEXT>
the house of balmain has presented its new designer 
for its ivoire line of luxury readytowear alistair blair of 
scotland 
he is wellknown in great britain having designed for jaeger 
and under his own label 
his sketches won me over said alain chevalier who as 
balmains resident has overseen a major financial restructuring 
this year 
chevalier said he based his choice announced friday on blairs 
creativity and experience which includes nine years in paris with 
couture houses like dior givenchy chloe and karl lagerfeld 
this is the latest in various french fashion companies bids to 
boost fashion excitement and sales with new designers 
the trend started in 1983 when karl lagerfeld made a splash at 
chanel reviving the old name with his creative ideas 
last summer gianfranco ferre took over as diors head designer 
the house of lanvin is looking for original couture creativity from 
claude montana 
and nina riccis readytowear got a fresh approach with another 
englishman philip waghorne 
erik mortensen balmains danishborn designer will keep his 
post as head of haute couture which he has occupied since pierre 
balmains death in 1982 
his last ivoire collection wednesday was a lowkeyed 
presentation of a few beautifully made outfits 
among the suits a standout was the black faille number with hot 
orange satin lapels turned back with a big button 
in the sparkly evening wear the hostess gown of gold guipure 
lace over a spangled stripe skirt had charm worthy of the new new 
york preference for taste over glitz 
there also were remarkable black knits pieced in swooping arcs 
buttoned up with gold and sporting tulipsplit skirts 
now fashion buffs will be watching for blairs october debut 
ive given up my own label in england said blair a 
francophile who grew up near glasgow and trained at st martins 
school of art 
i feel paris is indeed the fashion capital the place to be 
for any designer he said 
he wouldnt reveal his plans but his recent work shows a 
bright bouncy approach without being too wayout for a couture 
customer 
blair will move to paris for his new job but will continue to 
design for jaeger and ballantyne cashmeres 
his first balmain assignment is a trip to the united states next 
week to win american prestigestore buyers as yet balmain has 
little representation in us shops 
chevalier also announced plans for luxury readytowear 
expansion in the far east with stores coming up soon in hong kong 
bangkok and singapore 
the balmain label still has a classic image but no matter what 
creations blair comes up with the prices will remain in the 
mediumexpensive category about 1000 for a suit retail 
chevalier also announced there would be a less expensive 
subivoire line based on blairs creations as yet unnamed most 
big names exploit less expensive lines such as saint laurents 
variation it is about a third less than the regular luxury 
readytowear 
