<TEXT>
the government intends to deploy the armed forces to 
halt the arrival of tens of thousands of illegal immigrants 
the fiveparty governing coalition announced friday that navy 
ships will patrol italys coasts and army soldiers will be posted 
along the countrys northeastern border italy has about 4800 
miles of coast and 600 miles of borderland 
the government said the armed forces will work in collaboration 
with the police 
in recent years an estimated 100000 illegal immigrants mostly 
from third world countries have arrived in italy each year 
officials say estimates of the total number of illegal immigrants 
vary from 500000 to 15 million 
italy has had difficulty absorbing the arrivals because of job 
and housing shortages as well as inadequate public health and 
education services 
there has been a recent wave of violence against immigrants 
particularly in the popular tourist city of florence 
</TEXT>
