warnings will be required on overthecounter aspirin products 
advising women in the last three months of pregnancy not to use the 
products unless directed by a physician 
aspirin late in pregnancy can affect fetal circulation and 
uterine contractions and cause excessive bleeding during delivery 
an fda spokeswoman said friday 
