22 billion private investment would drop 73 percent in a puerto 
rican state the study said statehood would spell the end of an 
estimated 2 billion a year in tax benefits designed to encourage 
investment 
the island which currently has an 82 million ceiling on 
federal money for social programs would gain an additional 36 
billion in federal spending by the year 2000 
