once they start marching it becomes much tougher to stop 
them gronowski said but right now theyre still young and 
arent really on the move so weve got an opportunity to do 
something to control them 
mormon crickets which actually are relatives of grasshoppers 
and katydids got their name from an infestation in utah in the 
