<TEXT>
former national security adviser john 
poindexter was convicted today at his irancontra coverup trial of 
all five felony charges against him in the scandal that rocked the 
last two years of the reagan administration 
the jury delivered the verdict on one count of conspiracy two 
counts of obstructing congress and two counts of lying to congress 
the former national security adviser is the highestranking 
reagan administration official to be put on trial in the 
irancontra scandal the former president testified on videotape 
poindexter 53 faces up to 25 years in prison and fines of 
125 million us district court judge harold greene scheduled 
sentencing for june 11 
poindexter made no comment but his attorney richard beckler 
said the verdict would be appealed were going to keep fighting 
it as long as we can 
