25yearold foreman wayne mitchell read the verdicts 
guilty mitchell said as the clerk read each of the five 
criminal charges aloud 
there was silence in the courtroom as the first verdict was 
returned and then a murmur as mitchell continued to read guilty 
verdicts on each of the five counts 
he joins former aide oliver north and another reagan 
administration national security adviser robert mcfarlane as 
officials who stand convicted in irancontra 
the charges stem from efforts by officials in the reagan 
