the citys 5 marijuana ordinance takes effect only if a state or 
federal law bans abortion 
kim lane scheppele an assistant professor of political science 
at michigan calls the abortion measure the municipal equivalent 
of civil disobedience 
the provision which backers believe is unlike any other in the 
nation attracted no organized opposition and its passage surprised 
no one yet the voters also approved raising the marijuana fine 
from 5 to 25 
