here are the main issues and party 
positions in greeces national elections sunday 
economy greece has an inflation rate of about 178 percent and 
an estimated budget deficit of 156 billion the conservative new 
democracy wants to slash public spending streamline the public 
sector minimize state interference and attract private investment 
the panhellenic socialist movement pasok wants to improve public 
sector production but not cut spending the coalition of the left 
and progress promises tax reform public spending reform and 
measures to protect the buying power of wages 
defense new democracy regards nato membership and the four us 
military bases in greece as crucial for greeces defense pasok 
says greece should not blindly follow nato policies and says any 
future defense agreement with the united states should be put to a 
referendum the coalition wants to close the us bases and pull 
greece out of nato 
electoral law all parties seek changes in the election law to 
strengthen their own positions new democracy wants to make it 
easier to win a majority with less than 50 percent of the vote 
pasok and the coalition want to require a party to get more than 50 
percent of the vote to win a majority in parliament under the 
current law a party can win a majority in parliament with 47 
percent to 48 percent of the vote 
