<TEXT>
children those who most need protection 
from the law often become its victims legal experts said saturday 
the bitter fact is that the status of children in america has 
deteriorated over the past several decades us court of appeals 
judge patricia wald told about 400 lawyers judges and other 
professionals in the opening session of lawyers for children in 
the 1990s 
the conference on childrens legal rights was aimed at promoting 
what one lawyer called the practice of pediatric law 
the conference organized by the harvard law school children and 
family rights project was a nutsandbolts examination of what 
lawyers could and should do to help societys children 
according to howard davidson an american bar association director 
specializing in childrens issues 
the courts that children are involved with are often the worst 
in the system davidson said in an interview they should be 
the best 
unlike bankruptcy proceedings for example when theres time to 
examine every nuance of a case a juvenile court judge is lucky 
if he can put five minutes in to say whats this all about he 
said weve misplaced our priorities 
if juvenile courts were open to the public if people knew how 
resourcepoor how overwhelmed the system was i would hope they 
wouldnt stand for it davidson said 
the conferences panel discussions were more than an opportunity 
to trade horror stories about the system 
rather davidson said the goal was to provide practical 
knowledge for lawyers who represent children or who could volunteer 
to represent children through pro bono work services provided for 
free 
we want to be to children what pediatrics are to doctors he 
said 
one way of helping children is through guardian ad litem 
programs in which children in both abuse and juvenile delinquency 
cases are represented by an attorney davidson said 
