violence in the home she called for more intervention to protect 
women and their children 
a 1986 study by the hazelton foundation found that 63 percent of 
all boys and young men age 11 to 20 who had committed murder had 
killed the person battering their mother buel said 
theyve taken on the role that weve failed to do she said 
buel was herself a battered wife a single mother and former 
welfare recipient who survived through a social service network 
