cerebral palsy to a teenage mother he was placed in foster care 
at one year of age weighing 17 pounds when eugene was 10 the 
state finally got around to checking on his condition and removed 
him from the foster home he still weighed 17 pounds mcdonald said 
our law used to pretend that there was a benevolent aspect of 
society constantly working to improve the lot of these children 
wald told the conference now at least we admit that is not 
always so 
