<TEXT>
vice adm john m poindexter was regarded 
throughout his navy career as the consummate military aide a 
perfect man to carry out orders with a preciseness that bordered on 
brilliance 
yet he emerged as a national security adviser who would tell 
skeptical congressional committees investigating the irancontra 
affair that the buck stops here with me with regard to the 
decision to divert to the central american contras money made from 
arms sales to iran 
a man once decorated for his efficiency in handling paperwork 
poindexter was convicted saturday of felony charges that make the 
53yearold officer liable for a potential 25year prison term one 
of the charges tearing up paperwork 
when the jury decision was read indictmentbyindictment 
guilty verdictbyguilty verdict the career military man stood at 
attention before the bench rocking forward every so slightly as 
the count was rendered 
his wife an episcopal priest sat stoically beside the chief 
defense lawyers wife mrs poindexter remained still showing no 
emotion until it was over then she inclined her head every so 
slightly on the other womans shoulder an sighed quietly 
linda and john poindexter both from indiana were married in 
1958 two days after he finished first in his class at the us 
naval academy at annapolis he was also brigade commander one of 
only about a halfdozen men this century to graduate no 1 in both 
academics and leadership 
for 20 years she devoted her time to raising the couples five 
boys and when they started to leave home began studying for the 
ministry 
poindexter went on to earn a doctorate in nuclear physics and 
was on the navy fast track in 1981 when he was tapped to become 
military aide to former president reagans first national security 
adviser richard v allen 
when allen was replaced by william p clark jr poindexter 
stayed in the same role and subsequently was a deputy to nsc 
director robert c mcfarlane 
when mcfarlane left poindexter moved into the top nsc job and 
right into the irancontra caldron that was already swirling much 
of it around oliver north a marine lieutenant colonel with a 
natural flair for theatrics who was to emerge as a well known 
national figure a hero to some and a big drawing card at 
conservative fundraisers 
by contrast the jurors who were to convict poindexter indicated 
in their responses to questions during jury selection that his name 
let alone details of the charges against him barely registered 
on their mental radar screens 
poindexter has declined to give interviews since being 
implicated publicly in the affair but interviews with friends 
colleagues and some in congress and elsewhere who are not 
necessarily fond of the admiral have painted an almost universal 
picture of a man more versed in the scientific and military 
pursuits than politics and public relations 
in particular it was said that he never masted the art of 
dealing with congress or with the press 
as an ncs aide in 1985 he was credited within the inner circles 
of the white house with planning and supervising the bold midair 
interception of the plane carrying the hijackers of the achille 
lauro and diverting the plane to italy 
although unknown to the public at the time reagan is reported 
to have said i salute the admiral when he walked into the 
morning nsc briefing the next day 
he wasnt the kind of officer who would do something without 
authority adm daniel j murphy chief of staff to thenvice 
president bush from 1981 to 1985 said of poindexter in an 
interview more than three years ago 
yet it was the same poindexter who told an inquiring 
congressional panel the buck stops here with me i made the 
decision to divert arms sale money to the contras i thought i 
had the authority to do it i thought it was a good idea i was 
convinced the president would in the end think it was a good 
idea but i did not want him to be associated with the decision 
