midweek american petroleum institute inventory report would show 
substantial declines in gasoline stocks indicating rising demand 
but the report showed largerthanexpected us supplies of crude 
oil and heating oil but a smallerthanexpected gasoline supply 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
cattle and pork futures were mixed with pork rising sharply 
early in the week following a government report indicating lagging 
hog production this year however lower cash prices adversely 
affected pork future prices increased supplies of fed cattle 
weighed on livestock futures but prices were helped by light sales 
and higher prices for steers 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
grain and soybean futures were mixed in the aftermath of us 
agriculture department reports that farmers would increase corn 
production this year while soybean production would be cut back 
soybean prices after surging early in the week came under 
pressure because of slack export demand fears of a weekend freeze 
in the winter wheat crop area gave some support to wheat futures 
